    "We evaluated three types of context (Table 2).",
    "We define two baselines to assess model performance in our core and additional experiments: as lower bound we use a zero-shot prompting approach; as upper bound we use a fine-tuned sequence classifier trained on the full size of the training corpus.",
    "Fig. 4 shows the accuracy results for both baselines.",
    "The upper bound results exceed 96% accuracy for both models.",
    "The further-pretrained gbert models yield a minimal (statistically significant) advance of 0.4-0.6 accuracy points above the original gbert-base."
